OL,3,CVictims of infected blood scandal
OL,4,C'battling for truth'
OL,6,F"You can't sit down and go I'll give
OL,7,Fyou two hundred and fifty thousand
OL,8,Fpounds and that will cover the loss of
OL,9,Fyour career, the loss of your ability
OL,10,Fto become a mum, the loss of your
OL,11,Fability to become a grandma, because
OL,12,Fthat's never going to happen. The loss
OL,13,Fof your marriage."
OL,15,F"All sorts of things that I'm having
OL,16,Fto deal with every day and have for
OL,17,Fthe last thirty years", she adds.
OL,19,FRosemary Calder from lost her son
OL,20,FNicky after he was infected with HIV
OL,21,Fand Hepatitis C as a young boy.
